OL,3,GEast Midlands
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry but cloudy morning. Cloud
OL,6,Fbreaking from late morning allowing
OL,7,Fsunny spells to develop, before
OL,8,Fturning cloudy again in the afternoon.
OL,9,FWinds becoming light and variable,
OL,10,Fbreezy along the coast.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA dry and cloudy evening to
OL,13,Fstart, clear skies developing in the
OL,14,Fwest during the early hours. Winds
OL,15,Fremain light and variable.
OL,16,
OL,17,CTuesday:FA cloudy day with sunny spell
OL,18,Fin the afternoon and skies clearing
OL,19,Finto the evening. Winds light.
OL,20,FTemperatures generally average or
OL,21,Fslightly above.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
